{
  "name": "RPlog_Commander_Brand_Petitions_for_Pirates",
  "title": "Commander Brand Petitions for Pirates",
  "summary": "In a New Alderaan Senate antechamber, the FleetOps officer Commander Argon Brand meets the recently-returned Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard for an off-the-record briefing on a wave of Wookiee abductions. Delgard reveals that an informant inside Rendili and the Hutt Juuka point to a Trandoshan clan, the Bloodclaws, behind the forced-labor smuggling, and the two weigh options: arming the oppressed rival clans, smear campaigns against Rendili, and bolstering the Navy's presence at Kashyyyk. Argon pitches reviving the privateer model, granting letters of marque to private ship owners to harass slavers and Imperials in exchange for conditional pardons, and floats recruiting the wealthy, troubled Jedi Johanna te Danaan as a discreet backer. Delgard agrees the idea has merit if kept off the books, tasks Argon with quietly sounding out te Danaan and his Admiral, and the meeting ends on a cordial toast.",
